id: AIC-ASK-001-PY
type: component
owner: developer
extends:
  business: AIC-ASK-001
  language: aic-python-guidelines

component: AskCommand
file: python/ask/AskCommand/ask_command.py

implementation:
  - id: AIC-ASK-001-PY-I1
    intent: |
      Entry point is a Click command named ask().
      Accepts:
        --query: str      ← required, the question or fix request
        --fix: bool       ← optional, applies code changes
        --language: str   ← optional, scopes to one language
      No positional arguments.

  - id: AIC-ASK-001-PY-I2
    intent: |
      Phase 1 — Scope detection (deterministic).
      Discover all components from /business folder.
      Discover all languages from root folder.
      Match component names against query string.
      Match language names against query string.
      Build ScopeResult:
        components: list of matched component names
        language: matched language or None
        is_project_level: True if no component matched

  - id: AIC-ASK-001-PY-I3
    intent: |
      Phase 2 — Context assembly (deterministic).
      For each matched component:
        Read project.intent
        Read business/<Component>/module.intent
        Read <language>/<language>.intent if language matched
        Read all .intent files in <language>/<Component>/
        Read all code files in <language>/<Component>/
          (code files only in fix mode or when explicitly needed)
      For project level:
        Read project.intent
        Read all module.intent files in /business/
        No code files
      Assemble into structured prompt context string.

  - id: AIC-ASK-001-PY-I4
    intent: |
      Phase 3 — Prompt building (deterministic).
      Question mode prompt structure:
        Section 1: assembled intent context
        Section 2: code files if component scope
        Section 3: the query
        Section 4: instruction — answer clearly and concisely

      Fix mode prompt structure:
        Section 1: assembled intent context
        Section 2: existing code files with file paths as headers
        Section 3: the fix request
        Section 4: instruction —
          "Return fixed code for each file you modify.
           Format each file as:
           FILE: <relative/path/to/file>
           <complete fixed file content>
           END_FILE
           Only include files you actually changed."

  - id: AIC-ASK-001-PY-I5
    intent: |
      Phase 4 — AI call (LLM).
      Send prompt to configured AI provider.
      Receive response string.
      Question mode: print response directly to terminal.
      Fix mode: parse response into file blocks then write.

  - id: AIC-ASK-001-PY-I6
    intent: |
      Fix mode response parsing (deterministic).
      Parse AI response looking for FILE: markers.
      Pattern:
        FILE: python/UserService/user_service.py
        <code content>
        END_FILE
      Extract list of (file_path, code_content) tuples.
      If no FILE markers found — print raw response as fallback.
      Warn developer to apply manually.

  - id: AIC-ASK-001-PY-I7
    intent: |
      Fix mode file writing (deterministic).
      For each (file_path, code_content) tuple:
        Resolve full path from project root.
        Write code content to file.
        Print: "Fixed: <file_path>"
      If write fails print error but continue with other files.

  - id: AIC-ASK-001-PY-I8
    intent: |
      Fix mode auto-sync (deterministic + LLM via sync).
      After writing each fixed file:
        Detect which component and language from file path.
        Call run_sync(component_name, language) internally.
        Sync generates intent update suggestions automatically.
        Print: "Sync triggered for <component> — review suggestions"
      Developer then runs aic sync --approve to apply intent updates.

  - id: AIC-ASK-001-PY-I9
    intent: |
      Multi-language fix guard.
      If component exists in multiple language folders
      and --language flag not provided:
        List which languages the component exists in.
        Exit with message asking developer to specify --language.
        Fix cannot be applied to all languages simultaneously.

  - id: AIC-ASK-001-PY-I10
    intent: |
      Print summary after fix mode completes:
        "Files modified:"
          list each written file path
        "Sync status:"
          list each component where sync was triggered
        "Next steps:"
          aic sync <Component> --language <language> --approve
          aic status

error-handling:
  - NotInitialisedError         → exit code 1
  - GitNotInitialisedError      → exit code 1
  - ProviderNotConfiguredError  → exit code 1
  - ProviderCallError           → exit code 2, no files written
  - MultiLanguageFixError       → exit code 1, specify --language
  - NoMatchError                → exit code 0, list components
  - FileWriteError              → warn and continue, do not abort